WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.300
Oxford Bookworms Stage 1 Good-bye Mr. Hollywood by John Escott

00:10.300 --> 00:16.520
Read by Danica Fairman Published and copyright, Oxford University

00:16.520 --> 00:21.240
Press 1996

00:21.240 --> 00:27.400
Chapter 1 Mystery Girl

00:27.400 --> 00:36.760
It all began on a beautiful spring morning in a village called Whistler in Canada, a

00:36.760 --> 00:45.800
pretty little village in the mountains of British Columbia. There was a café in the village

00:45.800 --> 00:57.160
with tables outside and at one of these tables sat a young man. He finished his breakfast,

00:57.160 --> 01:07.480
drank his coffee, looked up into the blue sky and felt the warm sun on his face.

01:07.480 --> 01:14.440
Nick Lortz was a happy man. The waiter came up to his table.

01:14.440 --> 01:18.360
More coffee? He asked.

01:18.360 --> 01:25.880
Yeah, great! Said Nick. He gave the waiter his coffee cup.

01:25.880 --> 01:30.720
The waiter looked at the camera on the table.

01:30.720 --> 01:37.720
On vacation, he said, where are you from?

01:37.720 --> 01:43.720
San Francisco, Nick said. He laughed.

01:43.720 --> 01:54.720
But I'm not on vacation. I'm working. I'm a travel rider and I'm doing a book on mountains in North America.

01:54.720 --> 01:59.720
I've got some great pictures of your mountain.

01:59.720 --> 02:09.720
The two men looked up but Whistler Mountain behind the village. It looked very beautiful in the morning sun.

02:09.720 --> 02:15.720
Do you travel a lot then? asked the waiter.

02:15.720 --> 02:24.720
All the time, Nick said, I write books and I write for travel magazines.

02:24.720 --> 02:35.720
I write about everything. Different countries, towns, villages, rivers, mountains, people.

02:35.720 --> 02:39.720
The waiter looked over Nick's head.

02:39.720 --> 02:44.720
There's a girl across the street, he said.

02:44.720 --> 02:50.720
Do you know her? Nick turned his head and looked.

02:50.720 --> 02:53.720
No, I don't.

02:53.720 --> 02:59.720
Well, she knows you, I think. The waiter said.

02:59.720 --> 03:03.720
She's watching you very carefully.

03:03.720 --> 03:09.720
He gave Nick a smile. Have a nice day.

03:09.720 --> 03:15.720
He went away, back into the cafe.

03:15.720 --> 03:25.720
Nick looked at the girl across the street. She was about 25 and she was very pretty.

03:25.720 --> 03:31.720
She is watching me. Nick thought.

03:31.720 --> 03:37.720
Then the girl turned and looked in one of the shop windows.

03:37.720 --> 03:43.720
After a second or two, she looked back at Nick again.

03:43.720 --> 03:49.720
Nick watched her. She looks worried, he thought.

03:49.720 --> 03:55.720
What's she doing? Is she waiting for somebody?

03:55.720 --> 03:59.720
Suddenly the girl smiled.

03:59.720 --> 04:07.720
Then she walked across the street, came up to Nick's table and sat down.

04:07.720 --> 04:14.720
She put her bag down on the table. The bag was half open.

04:14.720 --> 04:21.720
Hi, I'm Jan. She said. Do you remember me?

04:21.720 --> 04:26.720
We met at a party in Toronto.

04:26.720 --> 04:31.720
Hi Jan, said Nick. He smiled.

04:31.720 --> 04:37.720
I'm Nick, but we didn't meet at a party in Toronto.

04:37.720 --> 04:43.720
I don't go to parties very often and never in Toronto.

04:43.720 --> 04:51.720
Oh, the girl said. But she didn't get up or move away.

04:51.720 --> 04:55.720
Have some coffee, said Nick.

04:55.720 --> 05:06.720
The story about the party in Toronto wasn't true, but it was a beautiful morning and she was a pretty girl.

05:06.720 --> 05:12.720
Maybe it was a party in Montreal or New York.

05:12.720 --> 05:14.720
The girl laughed.

05:14.720 --> 05:22.720
Okay, maybe it was. And yes, I'd love some coffee.

05:22.720 --> 05:26.720
When she had her coffee, Nick asked.

05:26.720 --> 05:32.720
What are you doing in Whistler? Or do you live here?

05:32.720 --> 05:43.720
Oh, no, she said. I'm just, er, just travelling through. And what are you doing here?

05:43.720 --> 05:52.720
I'm a travel writer, Nick said. And I'm writing a book about famous mountains.

05:52.720 --> 06:05.720
That's interesting, she said. But her face was worried, not interested. And she looked across the road again.

06:05.720 --> 06:13.720
A man with very short white hair walked across the road.

06:13.720 --> 06:19.720
He was about sixty years old, and he was tall and thin.

06:19.720 --> 06:22.720
The girl watched him.

06:22.720 --> 06:27.720
Are you waiting for someone? asked Nick.

06:27.720 --> 06:33.720
No, she said quickly. Then she asked.

06:33.720 --> 06:37.720
Where are you going next, Nick?

06:37.720 --> 06:44.720
To Vancouver, for three or four days, he said.

06:44.720 --> 06:48.720
When are you going? She asked.

06:48.720 --> 06:57.720
Later this morning, he said, there was a letter in the top of the girl's half-open bag.

06:57.720 --> 07:07.720
Nick could seize some of the writing, and he read it because he saw the word Vancouver.

07:07.720 --> 07:18.720
And we can meet at the Empress Hotel, Victoria, Vancouver Island, on Friday afternoon.

07:18.720 --> 07:24.720
So she's going to Vancouver too, he thought.

07:24.720 --> 07:30.720
Suddenly the girl said, do you like movies?

07:30.720 --> 07:37.720
Movies? Yes, I love movies, he said. Why?

07:37.720 --> 07:50.720
I know a man, and he loves movies, and going to the cinema, she said slowly.

07:50.720 --> 07:58.720
People call him Mr. Hollywood, she smiled at Nick.

07:58.720 --> 08:03.720
Can I call you Mr. Hollywood too?

08:03.720 --> 08:05.720
Nick laughed.

08:05.720 --> 08:08.720
Okay, he said.

08:08.720 --> 08:12.720
And what can I call you?

08:12.720 --> 08:15.720
She smiled again.

08:15.720 --> 08:20.720
Call me mystery girl, she said.

08:20.720 --> 08:25.720
That's a good name for you, said Nick.

08:25.720 --> 08:31.720
Just then, the man with white hair came into the café.

08:31.720 --> 08:39.720
He did not look at Nick or the girl, but he sat at a table near them.

08:39.720 --> 08:47.720
He asked the waiter for some breakfast, then he began to read a magazine.

08:47.720 --> 08:54.720
The girl looked the man, then quickly looked away again.

08:54.720 --> 08:58.720
Do you know him? Nick asked her.

08:58.720 --> 09:01.720
No, she said.

09:01.720 --> 09:05.720
She finished her coffee quickly and got up.

09:05.720 --> 09:09.720
I must go now, she said.

09:09.720 --> 09:13.720
Nick stood up too, nice too.

09:13.720 --> 09:23.720
He began, but the girl suddenly took his face between her hands and kissed him on the mouth.

09:24.720 --> 09:28.720
Drive carefully, Mr. Hollywood.

09:28.720 --> 09:35.720
Goodbye, she said, with a big, beautiful smile.

09:35.720 --> 09:42.720
Then she turned and walked quickly away.

09:42.720 --> 09:46.720
Nick sat down again and watched her.

09:46.720 --> 09:52.720
She walked down the road and into a big hotel.

09:52.720 --> 10:00.720
Now what, thought Nick, was that all about?

10:00.720 --> 10:06.720
The man with white hair watched Nick and waited.

10:06.720 --> 10:18.720
After four or five minutes, Nick finished his coffee, took his books and his camera, and left the café.

10:18.720 --> 10:27.720
His car was just outside the girl's hotel, and he walked slowly along the street to it.

10:27.720 --> 10:36.720
The man with white hair waited a second, then quickly followed Nick.

10:36.720 --> 10:45.720
From a window high up in the hotel, the girl looked down into the road.

10:45.720 --> 10:53.720
She saw Nick and the man with white hair about 50 yards behind him.

10:53.720 --> 11:03.720
Nick got into his car, and the man with white hair walked quickly to a red car across the street.

11:03.720 --> 11:14.720
Five seconds later, Nick drove away in his blue car, and the red car began to follow him.

11:14.720 --> 11:24.720
When the girl saw this, she smiled, then went to put some things in her travel bag.

11:24.720 --> 11:30.720
Chapter Two, A Hand in the Back

11:30.720 --> 11:41.720
That evening, in his hotel room in Vancouver, Nick could not stop thinking about the girl in the Whistler café.

11:42.720 --> 11:45.720
Why did she come and sit with him?

11:45.720 --> 11:57.720
She didn't know him, and that story about a party in Toronto wasn't true, and she was worried about something.

11:57.720 --> 11:59.720
But what?

11:59.720 --> 12:02.720
And that kiss?

12:02.720 --> 12:08.720
It was nice, of course, but why did she do it?

12:08.720 --> 12:15.720
Maybe she liked my face, Nick thought, or my brown eyes.

12:15.720 --> 12:21.720
But I'm not going to see her again, so it doesn't matter.

12:21.720 --> 12:24.720
Forget it.

12:24.720 --> 12:31.720
He put some money in his pocket, and went downstairs to the hotel restaurant.

12:31.720 --> 12:42.720
But there were no free tables, so he walked down to Gastown and found a restaurant there.

12:42.720 --> 12:46.720
After dinner, he went for a walk.

12:46.720 --> 12:59.720
Vancouver was a friendly city, and Nick liked walking through Gastown and Chinatown, looking in the shops and watching the people.

13:00.720 --> 13:06.720
It was nearly dark now, and it was a busy time of the evening.

13:06.720 --> 13:12.720
There were a lot of cars, and a lot of people.

13:12.720 --> 13:18.720
After a time, Nick began to walk back to his hotel.

13:18.720 --> 13:26.720
He came to a busy street, and waited with a small crowd of people to go across.

13:26.720 --> 13:31.720
A tall woman in a blue dress stood next to him.

13:31.720 --> 13:35.720
She turned and smiled at him.

13:35.720 --> 13:40.720
It's the first warm evening of spring, she said.

13:40.720 --> 13:45.720
It's nice to be out after the long, cold winter.

13:45.720 --> 13:48.720
Yeah, said Nick.

13:48.720 --> 13:51.720
It's great.

13:51.720 --> 14:00.720
Suddenly, there was a hand in his back, and the hand pushed Nick into the road.

14:00.720 --> 14:06.720
Nick fell on his face in front of a big, green car.

14:06.720 --> 14:15.720
People screamed, but the green car stopped only inches from Nick's head.

14:15.720 --> 14:23.720
The woman in the blue dress ran into the road and pulled Nick to his feet.

14:23.720 --> 14:25.720
Are you okay?

14:25.720 --> 14:26.720
What happened?

14:26.720 --> 14:28.720
She said.

14:28.720 --> 14:37.720
The driver of the green car shouted angrily at Nick, but Nick did not hear him.

14:38.720 --> 14:42.720
Somebody pushed me, he said to the woman.

14:42.720 --> 14:44.720
I didn't fall.

14:44.720 --> 14:47.720
Somebody pushed me.

14:47.720 --> 14:50.720
Pushed you, said the woman.

14:50.720 --> 14:56.720
Oh, I didn't see anybody.

14:56.720 --> 15:03.720
Nick looked at the faces of the people near him, but he didn't know them.

15:03.720 --> 15:06.720
Then he saw a man's back.

15:06.720 --> 15:13.720
The man was tall and thin and had very short, white hair.

15:13.720 --> 15:20.720
He walked quickly away down the street and did not look back.

15:20.720 --> 15:23.720
Hey, you!

15:23.720 --> 15:26.720
Nick shouted, wait!

15:26.720 --> 15:33.720
But the man did not stop, and he was soon lost in the crowds.

15:33.720 --> 15:36.720
Did he push you?

15:36.720 --> 15:39.720
Asked the woman in the blue dress.

15:39.720 --> 15:43.720
I don't know.

15:43.720 --> 15:45.720
Nick said.

15:45.720 --> 15:47.720
Do you know him?

15:47.720 --> 15:49.720
She asked.

15:49.720 --> 15:54.720
I don't know his name, Nick said.

15:54.720 --> 15:58.720
But I know that short, white hair.

15:58.720 --> 16:02.720
Now where did I see it before?

16:03.720 --> 16:07.720
The woman began to move away.

16:07.720 --> 16:11.720
I must get home, she said.

16:11.720 --> 16:14.720
Are you okay now?

16:14.720 --> 16:19.720
Yeah, I'm okay, Nick said.

16:19.720 --> 16:21.720
And thanks.

16:21.720 --> 16:24.720
Thanks for your help.

16:24.720 --> 16:29.720
That's okay, the woman smiled.

16:29.720 --> 16:33.720
Be careful now.

16:33.720 --> 16:40.720
Back in his hotel, Nick sat on his bed and thought.

16:40.720 --> 16:43.720
It was an accident.

16:43.720 --> 16:46.720
Nobody pushed me.

16:46.720 --> 16:49.720
It was an accident.

16:49.720 --> 16:52.720
Nobody wants to kill me.

16:52.720 --> 16:58.720
And there are hundreds of men in Vancouver with white hair.

16:58.720 --> 17:04.720
It was one o'clock in the morning, but Nick couldn't sleep.

17:04.720 --> 17:13.720
He listened to the cars in the road, and he looked at the night sky through his hotel room window.

17:13.720 --> 17:21.720
Then he sat at the table and tried to write some more of his book about mountains.

17:21.720 --> 17:25.720
But he couldn't think about his work.

17:25.720 --> 17:29.720
He got back into bed.

17:29.720 --> 17:35.720
There were four or five magazines in the hotel room.

17:35.720 --> 17:42.720
They were not very interesting, but Nick sat in bed and opened one.

17:42.720 --> 17:48.720
And saw a photo of mystery girl.

17:48.720 --> 17:52.720
He looked at the picture very carefully.

17:52.720 --> 17:57.720
But yes, it was her.

17:57.720 --> 18:03.720
Jan, the girl from the Whistler Cafe.

18:03.720 --> 18:15.720
She was next to a man of about 50 or 55, and they were in the garden of a big, expensive house.

18:15.720 --> 18:21.720
They smiled at the camera, and they looked very happy.

18:21.720 --> 18:31.720
Canadian millionaire Howard Hudson and his daughter Meg, it said under the picture.

18:31.720 --> 18:35.720
At their home in Toronto.

18:35.720 --> 18:41.720
Meg Hudson, not Jan, not mystery girl.

18:41.720 --> 18:46.720
Meg Hudson, the daughter of a millionaire.

18:47.720 --> 18:51.720
Nick read it again.

18:51.720 --> 18:56.720
Why did she come and sit with me in the cafe at Whistler?

18:56.720 --> 18:58.720
He thought.

18:58.720 --> 19:07.720
Millionaires daughters don't sit with strangers in cafes, and then give them a big kiss when they leave.

19:07.720 --> 19:10.720
Why did she do it?

19:10.720 --> 19:14.720
What did she want?

19:14.720 --> 19:21.720
He thought back to the cafe in Whistler, and the girl next to him at the table.

19:21.720 --> 19:24.720
Then he remembered something.

19:24.720 --> 19:30.720
He remembered a man at a table near them in the cafe.

19:30.720 --> 19:36.720
A tall, thin man, about 60 years old.

19:36.720 --> 19:42.720
A man with very short, white hair.

19:42.720 --> 19:48.720
Nick didn't sleep much that night.

19:48.720 --> 19:50.720
Chapter 3.

19:50.720 --> 19:55.720
A walk in the park.

19:55.720 --> 19:58.720
The next day was Thursday.

19:58.720 --> 20:05.720
Nick stayed in his hotel room and rode about mountains all morning.

20:05.720 --> 20:11.720
Then he drove to Stanley Park in the afternoon.

20:11.720 --> 20:15.720
He sat and read a book for an hour.

20:15.720 --> 20:20.720
Then he went for a walk under the tall trees.

20:20.720 --> 20:23.720
There was nobody here.

20:23.720 --> 20:29.720
It was quiet, and he could walk and sink.

20:29.720 --> 20:36.720
He thought about Meg Hudson and about the man with white hair.

20:36.720 --> 20:40.720
Did he know Meg Hudson?

20:40.720 --> 20:43.720
Did she know him?

20:43.720 --> 20:47.720
He remembered Meg Hudson's last words.

20:47.720 --> 20:54.720
Drive carefully, Mr. Hollywood.

20:54.720 --> 20:57.720
Why did she say that?

20:57.720 --> 21:02.720
Why did she call him Mr. Hollywood?

21:02.720 --> 21:06.720
He didn't understand any of it.

21:06.720 --> 21:10.720
Suddenly, he heard a noise.

21:10.720 --> 21:12.720
He stopped.

21:12.720 --> 21:16.720
That was a gun, he thought.

21:16.720 --> 21:21.720
There's somebody in the trees with a gun.

21:21.720 --> 21:24.720
There it is again.

21:24.720 --> 21:29.720
Then something hit the tree over his head.

21:29.720 --> 21:32.720
Somebody's shooting at me.

21:32.720 --> 21:34.720
Nick thought.

21:34.720 --> 21:37.720
He turned and ran.

21:37.720 --> 21:42.720
And somebody began to run after him.

21:42.720 --> 21:46.720
Nick ran through the trees.

21:46.720 --> 21:51.720
There was no sun in here, and it was half dark.

21:51.720 --> 21:53.720
And there were no people.

21:53.720 --> 21:56.720
Nobody to help him.

21:57.720 --> 22:01.720
I must get to my car, Nick thought.

22:01.720 --> 22:06.720
Find some people, the police.

22:06.720 --> 22:09.720
He ran on.

22:09.720 --> 22:16.720
He could still hear the gun man behind him, so he ran faster.

22:16.720 --> 22:22.720
After three or four minutes, he stopped and listened.

22:23.720 --> 22:25.720
Nothing.

22:25.720 --> 22:28.720
It was all quiet.

22:28.720 --> 22:31.720
Nick was afraid.

22:31.720 --> 22:33.720
What's happening?

22:33.720 --> 22:35.720
He thought.

22:35.720 --> 22:39.720
Why is somebody shooting at me?

22:39.720 --> 22:49.720
First a hand pushes me in front of a car, and now somebody shooting at me.

22:49.720 --> 22:57.720
He waited another second or two, then walked quickly back to his car.

22:57.720 --> 23:00.720
He was very careful.

23:00.720 --> 23:04.720
He looked and listened all the time.

23:04.720 --> 23:11.720
But nobody came out of the trees, and nobody shot at him.

23:11.720 --> 23:14.720
Then he saw people.

23:14.720 --> 23:17.720
Women with young children.

23:17.720 --> 23:20.720
Some boys with a football.

23:20.720 --> 23:23.720
Two men with a dog.

23:23.720 --> 23:26.720
He began to feel better.

23:26.720 --> 23:30.720
Nobody can shoot me now, he thought.

23:30.720 --> 23:35.720
Not with all these people here.

23:35.720 --> 23:41.720
Ten minutes later, he was back at his car.

23:41.720 --> 23:44.720
There was a ladder on the window.

23:44.720 --> 23:46.720
Nick read it.

23:46.720 --> 23:55.720
It said, I'm going to kill you, Mr. Hollywood.

23:55.720 --> 23:59.720
Nick drove to the nearest police station.

23:59.720 --> 24:02.720
He waited for half an hour.

24:02.720 --> 24:09.720
Then a tired young policeman took him into a small room.

24:09.720 --> 24:15.720
Nick told his story, and the policeman wrote it all down.

24:15.720 --> 24:20.720
So, what are you going to do?

24:20.720 --> 24:23.720
Asked Nick.

24:23.720 --> 24:27.720
Nothing, said the policeman.

24:27.720 --> 24:38.720
Nothing, said Nick, but somebody shot at me and, Mr. Lord's, the policeman said,

24:38.720 --> 24:40.720
tiredly.

24:40.720 --> 24:45.720
How many people are there in this town with guns?

24:45.720 --> 24:53.720
I don't know, said Nick, but you didn't see the gun man.

24:53.720 --> 24:55.720
Was it a man?

24:55.720 --> 24:56.720
A boy?

24:56.720 --> 24:58.720
A woman?

24:58.720 --> 25:00.720
Color of eyes?

25:00.720 --> 25:01.720
Long hair?

25:01.720 --> 25:02.720
Short hair?

25:02.720 --> 25:07.720
You don't know, because you didn't see anybody.

25:07.720 --> 25:11.720
Maybe it was an old girlfriend.

25:11.720 --> 25:18.720
Maybe somebody doesn't like your travel books, Mr. Lord's.

25:18.720 --> 25:23.720
But what about the man with white hair in Whistler?

25:23.720 --> 25:25.720
Said Nick.

25:25.720 --> 25:31.720
The girl, Meg Hudson, called me Mr. Hollywood in the cafe.

25:31.720 --> 25:34.720
And this man heard her.

25:34.720 --> 25:41.720
And now I get a letter to Mr. Hollywood on my car.

25:41.720 --> 25:46.720
Who is this Mr. Hollywood?

25:46.720 --> 25:53.720
We all want answers to our questions, Mr. Lord's, the policeman said.

25:53.720 --> 25:57.720
But we don't always get them.

25:57.720 --> 26:03.720
Questions, but no answers.

26:04.720 --> 26:09.720
Nick walked out of the police station and drove to his hotel.

26:09.720 --> 26:14.720
He was angry and afraid.

26:14.720 --> 26:19.720
How did the man with white hair find me in Vancouver?

26:19.720 --> 26:21.720
He thought.

26:21.720 --> 26:24.720
Did he follow me from Whistler?

26:24.720 --> 26:27.720
Is he following me now?

26:27.720 --> 26:31.720
Maybe he's staying at my hotel, too.

26:32.720 --> 26:39.720
In the next room, with his gun.

26:39.720 --> 26:41.720
Chapter 4

26:41.720 --> 26:46.720
The man with white hair.

26:46.720 --> 26:51.720
Nick stopped his car in front of the hotel.

26:51.720 --> 26:54.720
He looked carefully before he got out.

26:54.720 --> 26:59.720
But there was nobody with white hair near the hotel.

26:59.720 --> 27:06.720
He half ran through the hotel doors and went to the desk inside.

27:06.720 --> 27:11.720
I'm looking for a man with very short white hair.

27:11.720 --> 27:14.720
He said to the woman behind the desk.

27:14.720 --> 27:17.720
He's staying here, I think.

27:17.720 --> 27:24.720
He's about sixty years old and he's tall and thin.

27:24.720 --> 27:28.720
The woman did not look very interested.

27:28.720 --> 27:33.720
There are a lot of visitors in the hotel.

27:33.720 --> 27:34.720
She said.

27:34.720 --> 27:37.720
Do you know his name?

27:37.720 --> 27:40.720
No, I don't.

27:40.720 --> 27:41.720
Nick said.

27:41.720 --> 27:46.720
He's a friend of a friend, you see.

27:46.720 --> 27:52.720
He arrived in Vancouver yesterday and I must find him.

27:52.720 --> 27:55.720
It's very important.

27:55.720 --> 27:58.720
Please help me.

27:58.720 --> 28:02.720
The woman looked at him.

28:02.720 --> 28:07.720
There are three hundred and fifty rooms in this hotel.

28:07.720 --> 28:09.720
She said.

28:09.720 --> 28:14.720
And maybe thirty or forty men with white hair.

28:14.720 --> 28:18.720
How can I remember all their names?

28:18.720 --> 28:22.720
She turned away to answer a telephone call.

28:22.720 --> 28:26.720
Nick walked away from the desk.

28:26.720 --> 28:29.720
A drink, he thought.

28:29.720 --> 28:32.720
I need a drink.

28:32.720 --> 28:40.720
He went into the hotel bar, got a drink, and sat down at a table.

28:40.720 --> 28:44.720
So, what do I do now?

28:44.720 --> 28:47.720
He thought.

28:47.720 --> 28:51.720
And then he remembered something.

28:51.720 --> 28:59.720
A letter in the girl's half-open bag in the Whistler Cafe.

28:59.720 --> 29:10.720
And we can meet at the Empress Hotel, Victoria, Vancouver Island on Friday afternoon.

29:10.720 --> 29:15.720
And tomorrow was Friday.

29:15.720 --> 29:27.720
I'm going to Victoria on Vancouver Island, he thought, to the Empress Hotel.

29:27.720 --> 29:31.720
Nick had dinner in the hotel that evening.

29:31.720 --> 29:41.720
He finished eating and got up from his table and saw the man with white hair.

29:41.720 --> 29:44.720
Nick moved quickly.

29:44.720 --> 29:47.720
The man was at the hotel desk.

29:47.720 --> 29:54.720
Nick could see the white head above the other heads near the desk.

29:54.720 --> 29:58.720
Excuse me, said Nick.

29:58.720 --> 30:02.720
He pushed past the people in the hotel restaurant.

30:02.720 --> 30:08.720
A small boy ran in front of him, and Nick ran into him.

30:08.720 --> 30:12.720
The boy and Nick fell down on the floor.

30:12.720 --> 30:15.720
The boy began to cry.

30:15.720 --> 30:18.720
Hey, said a woman behind Nick.

30:18.720 --> 30:22.720
I'm very sorry, said Nick.

30:22.720 --> 30:25.720
He got up and helped the boy to his feet.

30:25.720 --> 30:27.720
Are you okay?

30:27.720 --> 30:29.720
He asked the boy.

30:29.720 --> 30:34.720
Be more careful next time, said the woman.

30:34.720 --> 30:37.720
Nick moved away quickly.

30:37.720 --> 30:44.720
But when he looked back at the hotel desk, he couldn't see the man with white hair.

30:44.720 --> 30:48.720
He pushed through the crowd of people.

30:48.720 --> 30:53.720
That man, he shouted at the woman behind the desk.

30:53.720 --> 30:57.720
That man with short white hair.

30:57.720 --> 31:00.720
Where did he go?

31:00.720 --> 31:03.720
The woman looked at Nick.

31:03.720 --> 31:07.720
Mr. Vickers, she said.

31:07.720 --> 31:10.720
I don't know.

31:10.720 --> 31:15.720
Vickers, is that his name, said Nick?

31:15.720 --> 31:18.720
What's his room number?

31:18.720 --> 31:24.720
I'm sorry, I can't tell you that, the woman said.

31:24.720 --> 31:28.720
But I need to begin Nick.

31:28.720 --> 31:33.720
The woman turned away to answer the telephone.

31:33.720 --> 31:39.720
After a second or two, Nick went upstairs to his room.

31:40.720 --> 31:43.720
Vickers, he thought.

31:43.720 --> 31:48.720
Does Meg Hudson know Mr. Vickers?

31:48.720 --> 31:57.720
I need some answers, and I need them quickly.

31:57.720 --> 32:02.720
Chapter 5, Vancouver Island.

32:02.720 --> 32:08.720
Tow Austin was about 23 miles south of Vancouver.

32:08.720 --> 32:17.720
Nick drove there in his car the next morning for the 1 o'clock ferry to Vancouver Island.

32:17.720 --> 32:21.720
Every five minutes, he looked behind him.

32:21.720 --> 32:24.720
The road was busy.

32:24.720 --> 32:31.720
Black cars, white cars, red cars, green cars.

32:31.720 --> 32:35.720
Maybe Vickers was in one of them.

32:35.720 --> 32:42.720
At Tow Austin, Nick drove his car onto the ferry.

32:42.720 --> 32:48.720
There were a lot of cars and crowds of people.

32:48.720 --> 32:55.720
Nick got out of his car and walked up and down the ship.

32:55.720 --> 33:02.720
He looked for a man with white hair, but he didn't see one.

33:02.720 --> 33:08.720
Soon the ferry began to move, and Nick felt better.

33:08.720 --> 33:14.720
He found the ferry restaurant and got something to eat.

33:14.720 --> 33:17.720
More people came in.

33:17.720 --> 33:23.720
Nick looked at the faces of all the older men.

33:23.720 --> 33:30.720
Some had hats on, so he looked for somebody tall and thin.

33:30.720 --> 33:33.720
But there was nobody.

33:33.720 --> 33:38.720
Maybe he's not on the ferry, Nick thought.

33:38.720 --> 33:43.720
Maybe he's back in Vancouver.

33:43.720 --> 33:48.720
Later, Nick walked around the ship again.

33:48.720 --> 33:58.720
Once, he thought he saw the man with white hair in the crowds, but he could not be sure.

33:58.720 --> 34:08.720
90 minutes after leaving Tow Austin, the ferry arrived at Swartz Bay on Vancouver Island,

34:08.720 --> 34:13.720
and Nick went back down to his car.

34:13.720 --> 34:20.720
Swartz Bay was 20 miles north of Victoria.

34:20.720 --> 34:28.720
Nick drove quickly, and again looked behind him every four or five minutes.

34:28.720 --> 34:36.720
Once, he saw a red car about 200 yards behind him.

34:36.720 --> 34:42.720
Did I see that car on the road from Vancouver to Tow Austin?

34:42.720 --> 34:44.720
He thought.

34:44.720 --> 35:00.720
He drove more slowly, but the red car still stayed 200 yards behind him, and Nick couldn't see the driver's face or hair.

35:00.720 --> 35:12.720
Soon, he was in the busy streets of Victoria, and Nick didn't see the red car behind him again.

35:12.720 --> 35:19.720
Victoria was a city of gardens and beautiful old buildings.

35:19.720 --> 35:29.720
Nick liked Victoria very much, but today he wasn't interested in gardens or buildings.

35:29.720 --> 35:38.720
He found the Empress Hotel, went inside, and walked across to the desk.

35:38.720 --> 35:40.720
Can I help you?

35:40.720 --> 35:44.720
A young man asked Nick.

35:44.720 --> 35:50.720
I'm meeting a friend here this afternoon, said Nick.

35:50.720 --> 35:52.720
Miss Hudson.

35:52.720 --> 35:56.720
Hudson, said the young man.

35:56.720 --> 35:58.720
Wait a minute.

35:58.720 --> 36:02.720
He went away and came back.

36:02.720 --> 36:08.720
Sorry, but there's no Miss Hudson staying here.

36:08.720 --> 36:12.720
Nick took something from his pocket.

36:12.720 --> 36:20.720
It was the photograph of Meg and her father from the magazine.

36:20.720 --> 36:24.720
This is her, he said.

36:24.720 --> 36:28.720
The young man looked at the picture.

36:28.720 --> 36:30.720
Oh, right.

36:30.720 --> 36:35.720
You mean Howard Hudson's daughter, he said.

36:35.720 --> 36:41.720
She's not staying here, but I saw her 10 or 15 minutes ago.

36:41.720 --> 36:45.720
She was with somebody, a man.

36:45.720 --> 36:49.720
He asked me about the tea room.

36:49.720 --> 36:52.720
The tea room, said Nick.

36:52.720 --> 36:56.720
Where's that?

36:56.720 --> 37:02.720
The man with short white hair was tired.

37:02.720 --> 37:06.720
He couldn't sleep, and he couldn't eat.

37:06.720 --> 37:12.720
He thought about only one thing, all the time.

37:12.720 --> 37:20.720
He drove and he watched, and he waited, and he followed.

37:20.720 --> 37:31.720
When he drove into Victoria, the streets were busy, and suddenly he lost the blue car in front of him.

37:31.720 --> 37:39.720
Angrily, he drove around the city, passed all the big hotels.

37:39.720 --> 37:43.720
I must find him, he said.

37:43.720 --> 37:48.720
I must do it today.

37:48.720 --> 37:59.720
Then he saw the Empress Hotel, and in the street outside it, a blue car.

37:59.720 --> 38:08.720
He drove past the hotel, left his car, and ran back down the street.

38:08.720 --> 38:15.720
He went across the road, and walked past the downstairs windows.

38:15.720 --> 38:21.720
There was a big room with tables and chairs, and a lot of people.

38:21.720 --> 38:26.720
He looked carefully at all the faces.

38:26.720 --> 38:30.720
There she is, he said suddenly.

38:30.720 --> 38:34.720
There were two men with the girl.

38:34.720 --> 38:44.720
He couldn't see their faces, only the backs of their heads, but one of the men was in a green shirt.

38:44.720 --> 38:50.720
Mr. Hollywood, the man said, and smiled.

38:50.720 --> 38:55.720
Goodbye, Mr. Hollywood.

38:55.720 --> 39:02.720
People in the street turned to look at him, but the man did not see them.

39:02.720 --> 39:10.720
He walked up to the doors of the hotel, and put a hand into his pocket.

39:10.720 --> 39:19.720
Inside, the gun was cold and hard.

39:19.720 --> 39:27.720
Chapter 6 A Tea Party

39:27.720 --> 39:33.720
Nick looked through the doors of the tea room in the Empress Hotel.

39:33.720 --> 39:38.720
Meg Hudson sat at a table with a man.

39:38.720 --> 39:44.720
The man was about thirty, or maybe a year or two younger.

39:44.720 --> 39:49.720
He was tall and brown from the sun.

39:49.720 --> 39:56.720
He wore a white shirt, white trousers, and white shoes.

39:56.720 --> 40:01.720
He said something to Meg, and she laughed.

40:01.720 --> 40:05.720
She looked very happy.

40:05.720 --> 40:09.720
A waiter came up to Nick.

40:09.720 --> 40:13.720
Can I get you some tea? He asked.

40:13.720 --> 40:17.720
No thanks, said Nick.

40:17.720 --> 40:25.720
I'm with the two people over there, and he walked across to Meg's table.

40:25.720 --> 40:30.720
Hello, mystery girl, said Nick.

40:30.720 --> 40:35.720
Remember me? We met at Whistler.

40:35.720 --> 40:43.720
Your name was Jan then, but maybe today it's Meg Hudson.

40:43.720 --> 40:47.720
Meg Hudson looked up at him.

40:47.720 --> 40:53.720
Oh, she said, and her face went red.

40:53.720 --> 40:58.720
Who is this, Meg? asked the man.

40:58.720 --> 41:02.720
This is Nick, said Meg.

41:02.720 --> 41:09.720
He's a writer. Nick, this is Craig Winters.

41:09.720 --> 41:16.720
Sometimes called Mr. Hollywood, said Nick.

41:16.720 --> 41:21.720
Maybe, but how did you know that?

41:21.720 --> 41:24.720
Asked Craig Winters.

41:24.720 --> 41:32.720
I guessed, said Nick, and I think I'm beginning to understand.

41:32.720 --> 41:37.720
Can I ask you a question, Mr. Winters?

41:37.720 --> 41:41.720
Does somebody want to kill you?

41:41.720 --> 41:45.720
Craig Winters' face went white.

41:45.720 --> 41:49.720
Kill me.

41:49.720 --> 41:54.720
What are you talking about? asked Meg.

41:54.720 --> 42:01.720
Before I tell you, answer this question please, said Nick.

42:01.720 --> 42:10.720
You called me, Mr. Hollywood, in Whistler, and you wanted the man at the next table,

42:10.720 --> 42:18.720
the man with white hair, to hear you. Is that right?

42:18.720 --> 42:22.720
Meg Hudson did not answer at first.

42:22.720 --> 42:25.720
Then she said quietly,

42:25.720 --> 42:27.720
Yes.

42:27.720 --> 42:31.720
Why? asked Nick.

42:31.720 --> 42:36.720
I wanted him to follow you, and not me.

42:36.720 --> 42:41.720
Why? Nick asked again.

42:41.720 --> 42:50.720
I think he's a detective, said Meg, and I think he's working for my father.

42:50.720 --> 42:56.720
I saw him soon after I left Toronto. He followed me.

42:56.720 --> 43:01.720
Meg put her hand on Craig Winters' arm.

43:01.720 --> 43:04.720
My father doesn't like Craig.

43:04.720 --> 43:10.720
A month ago, he told me not to see Craig again.

43:10.720 --> 43:14.720
I'm not happy, and he knows that.

43:14.720 --> 43:18.720
I think he guessed that I'm meeting Craig.

43:18.720 --> 43:23.720
And now, he wants to find Craig, and stop him seeing me.

43:23.720 --> 43:29.720
Stop him, said Nick, or kill him.

43:29.720 --> 43:34.720
No, Meg Hudson said, Daddy doesn't.

43:34.720 --> 43:42.720
The man with white hair pushed me in front of a car in Vancouver, Nick told her.

43:42.720 --> 43:46.720
And he shot at me in Stanley Park.

43:46.720 --> 43:49.720
What? said Meg.

43:49.720 --> 43:55.720
Tell, tell me about this man with white hair?

43:55.720 --> 43:58.720
Winter said suddenly.

43:58.720 --> 44:01.720
Nick looked at him.

44:01.720 --> 44:07.720
He was about 60, and he's tall and thin, he said.

44:07.720 --> 44:10.720
Do you know his name?

44:10.720 --> 44:12.720
Asked Winters.

44:12.720 --> 44:16.720
Vicars, said Nick.

44:16.720 --> 44:20.720
Craig Winters suddenly looked ill.

44:20.720 --> 44:26.720
Did he, did he follow you to Victoria?

44:26.720 --> 44:29.720
Did he follow you here?

44:29.720 --> 44:33.720
I don't know, said Nick.

44:33.720 --> 44:36.720
He watched Winters.

44:36.720 --> 44:39.720
You're afraid of him.

44:39.720 --> 44:41.720
Why?

44:41.720 --> 44:48.720
Why does this man, Vicars, want to kill you, Winters?

44:48.720 --> 44:54.720
Before Craig Winters could answer, Meg's face went white.

44:54.720 --> 44:56.720
Oh no!

44:56.720 --> 44:59.720
Vicars said, Look!

44:59.720 --> 45:01.720
Look over there!

45:01.720 --> 45:04.720
By the door!

45:04.720 --> 45:09.720
Nick and Craig Winters turned to look.

45:09.720 --> 45:15.720
At the door of the T-room, stood the man with white hair.

45:15.720 --> 45:25.720
He looked up and down the room, and then he saw them, and began to walk across to their table.

45:25.720 --> 45:28.720
And was in his pocket.

45:28.720 --> 45:35.720
For a second or two, the three people at the table did not move.

45:35.720 --> 45:40.720
Then Craig Winters jumped to his feet.

45:40.720 --> 45:43.720
That's Mr. Hollywood!

45:43.720 --> 45:48.720
He screamed, That man there!

45:48.720 --> 45:53.720
And he pointed at Nick.

45:53.720 --> 46:00.720
The man's hand came out of his pocket, with a gun.

46:00.720 --> 46:04.720
This is for Anna!

46:04.720 --> 46:07.720
He shouted.

46:07.720 --> 46:11.720
Nick moved very fast.

46:11.720 --> 46:19.720
The T-table went over, and Nick was down on the floor in a second.

46:19.720 --> 46:26.720
The shot went over his head, and Meg screamed.

46:26.720 --> 46:34.720
At the same time, Craig Winters shouted out, and put a hand on his arm.

46:34.720 --> 46:38.720
There was blood on his white shirt.

46:38.720 --> 46:48.720
Then more people began to scream, and two waiters pulled the man with white hair down onto the floor.

46:48.720 --> 46:51.720
Get the police!

46:51.720 --> 46:55.720
Somebody shouted.

46:55.720 --> 46:58.720
Chapter 7.

46:58.720 --> 47:03.720
At the police station.

47:03.720 --> 47:06.720
It was 7.30 pm.

47:06.720 --> 47:11.720
Nick and Meg were in a room at the police station.

47:11.720 --> 47:18.720
The man called Vickers, was in a different room, with three detectives.

47:18.720 --> 47:21.720
There was a doctor with him too.

47:21.720 --> 47:26.720
Craig Winters was at the hospital.

47:26.720 --> 47:33.720
The door opened, and the detective came in with two cups of coffee.

47:33.720 --> 47:39.720
He put them down on the table, and turned to go out again.

47:39.720 --> 47:43.720
Detective Edmonds, Meg said.

47:43.720 --> 47:45.720
Did the hospital call?

47:45.720 --> 47:49.720
Is Craig going to be alright?

47:49.720 --> 47:53.720
Winters, Detective Edmonds said,

47:53.720 --> 47:58.720
Yes, he is going to be okay.

47:58.720 --> 48:01.720
Can I call the hospital now?

48:01.720 --> 48:03.720
Asked Meg.

48:03.720 --> 48:07.720
I'd like you to wait, said Edmonds.

48:07.720 --> 48:11.720
Detective Keet is going to be here in a minute.

48:11.720 --> 48:18.720
He's just coming from the airport, and he looked through the open door.

48:18.720 --> 48:23.720
Ah, here he is now.

48:23.720 --> 48:32.720
A second detective came into the room, and behind him was a tall man with dark hair.

48:32.720 --> 48:36.720
Meg stood up quickly.

48:36.720 --> 48:39.720
Daddy, she cried.

48:39.720 --> 48:42.720
What are you doing here?

48:42.720 --> 48:50.720
The police called me, said Howard Hudson, and I flew here at once.

48:50.720 --> 48:55.720
Detective Keet met me at the airport.

48:55.720 --> 48:58.720
Now sit down, Meg.

48:58.720 --> 49:01.720
I want you to listen to me.

49:01.720 --> 49:05.720
He did not look at Nick.

49:05.720 --> 49:11.720
Meg sat down, and her father took her hands.

49:11.720 --> 49:18.720
Meg, last week Johnny Vickers came to my house.

49:18.720 --> 49:22.720
He wanted to talk about his daughter.

49:22.720 --> 49:26.720
You remember Anna, Meg?

49:26.720 --> 49:34.720
Three months ago, she jumped off a bridge in Boston and died.

49:34.720 --> 49:42.720
She was young, beautiful, rich, and she didn't want to live.

49:42.720 --> 49:44.720
Why?

49:44.720 --> 49:53.720
Because she loved a man, and the man took her money, ran away, and left her.

49:53.720 --> 49:58.720
And the man was called, no, said Meg.

49:58.720 --> 50:00.720
No!

50:00.720 --> 50:02.720
Yes, Meg.

50:02.720 --> 50:04.720
Yes.

50:04.720 --> 50:09.720
He was called, Mr. Hollywood.

50:09.720 --> 50:11.720
No!

50:11.720 --> 50:13.720
Shouted Meg.

50:13.720 --> 50:16.720
She began to cry.

50:16.720 --> 50:22.720
That's right, Ms. Hudson, said Detective Keet quietly.

50:22.720 --> 50:28.720
To you, he gave the name Craig Winters.

50:28.720 --> 50:34.720
When Anna Vickers knew him, he was Carl Windsor.

50:34.720 --> 50:43.720
But he liked all his, uh, girlfriends, to call him Mr. Hollywood.

50:43.720 --> 50:53.720
He took nearly $50,000 from Anna Vickers, and there was a girl before that.

50:53.720 --> 50:57.720
No, it's not true!

50:57.720 --> 50:59.720
Meg shouted.

50:59.720 --> 51:03.720
It is true, Meg, said her father.

51:03.720 --> 51:10.720
Winters, Windsor, gets all his money from rich men's daughters.

51:10.720 --> 51:13.720
Johnny Vickers loved his daughter.

51:13.720 --> 51:18.720
He went to her house in Boston after she died.

51:18.720 --> 51:26.720
He read her letters, and learned about the money, and the name, Mr. Hollywood.

51:26.720 --> 51:33.720
And when he came to my house, I told him about you, Meg.

51:33.720 --> 51:42.720
I said, my daughter's got a new boyfriend, and she calls him Mr. Hollywood.

51:42.720 --> 51:47.720
I don't like him, but I can't stop her.

51:47.720 --> 51:51.720
She's going away to meet him next week, I think.

51:51.720 --> 51:54.720
What can I do?

51:54.720 --> 52:02.720
Johnny put his hand on my arm, and he said, don't be afraid for your daughter.

52:02.720 --> 52:10.720
I'm going to find that man, and stop him.

52:10.720 --> 52:13.720
Meg said nothing.

52:13.720 --> 52:16.720
Her face was very white.

52:16.720 --> 52:21.720
For a minute or two, nobody spoke.

52:21.720 --> 52:24.720
Then Detective Edmonds said,

52:24.720 --> 52:28.720
Vickers told us all about it, Miss Hudson.

52:28.720 --> 52:34.720
He followed you to Whistler, and saw you with...

52:34.720 --> 52:45.720
Nick began to understand, with me in the café, and Meg called me Mr. Hollywood.

52:45.720 --> 52:49.720
Howard Hudson looked at Nick.

52:49.720 --> 52:53.720
You're the travel writer guy, right?

52:53.720 --> 52:55.720
Lord's.

52:55.720 --> 52:59.720
Nick Lord's, said Nick.

52:59.720 --> 53:02.720
Vickers nearly killed me.

53:02.720 --> 53:05.720
He shot at me twice, and...

53:05.720 --> 53:10.720
But Howard Hudson was not very interested in Nick.

53:10.720 --> 53:14.720
He looked at his daughter again.

53:14.720 --> 53:18.720
How much money did you give him, Meg?

53:18.720 --> 53:22.720
He said, I...

53:22.720 --> 53:28.720
I gave him $25,000.

53:28.720 --> 53:30.720
Said Meg.

53:30.720 --> 53:36.720
Only for two or three months, he said, then he...

53:36.720 --> 53:40.720
She began to cry again.

53:40.720 --> 53:48.720
Well, you can say goodbye to that money, said Hudson angrily.

53:48.720 --> 53:52.720
What's going to happen to Vickers?

53:52.720 --> 53:55.720
Nick asked Detective Edmonds.

53:55.720 --> 54:00.720
Hospital, I think, said Edmonds.

54:00.720 --> 54:07.720
Okay, he shot at you, and about 50 people saw him.

54:07.720 --> 54:10.720
But he's not a well man.

54:10.720 --> 54:17.720
The doctors are going to put him away in a hospital.

54:17.720 --> 54:20.720
Howard Hudson stood up.

54:20.720 --> 54:22.720
Okay, Meg.

54:22.720 --> 54:25.720
I'm going to take you home.

54:25.720 --> 54:30.720
My plane is waiting at the airport.

54:30.720 --> 54:33.720
Meg followed her father to the door.

54:33.720 --> 54:37.720
Then she remembered Nick, and turned.

54:37.720 --> 54:40.720
I'm sorry, she said.

54:40.720 --> 54:43.720
I got you into all this.

54:43.720 --> 54:47.720
I called you Mr. Hollywood.

54:47.720 --> 54:49.720
That was wrong.

54:49.720 --> 54:51.720
But I didn't know.

54:51.720 --> 54:54.720
It's okay, said Nick.

54:54.720 --> 54:57.720
You know everything now.

54:57.720 --> 55:02.720
And it's better to learn it now than not later.

55:02.720 --> 55:08.720
$50,000 later.

55:09.720 --> 55:11.720
Chapter 8.

55:11.720 --> 55:14.720
A nice smile.

55:14.720 --> 55:20.720
Nick took the evening ferry back to Vancouver.

55:20.720 --> 55:28.720
He was tired and hungry, so he went down to get some dinner in the ferry restaurant.

55:28.720 --> 55:34.720
The restaurant was busy, and there was only one free table.

55:34.720 --> 55:39.720
Nick sat down quickly and began to eat.

55:39.720 --> 55:51.720
I must get back to work tomorrow, he thought, and forget about millionaires, daughters, and men with guns.

55:51.720 --> 55:53.720
Excuse me?

55:53.720 --> 55:55.720
Somebody said.

55:55.720 --> 55:58.720
Can I sit with you?

55:58.720 --> 56:01.720
Nick looked up.

56:01.720 --> 56:05.720
There was a pretty girl next to his table.

56:05.720 --> 56:08.720
He got up.

56:08.720 --> 56:12.720
It's okay, he said.

56:12.720 --> 56:15.720
You can have this table.

56:15.720 --> 56:17.720
I don't want it.

56:17.720 --> 56:20.720
And he began to move away.

56:20.720 --> 56:25.720
Please don't go, the girl said.

56:25.720 --> 56:28.720
Stay and finish your dinner.

56:28.720 --> 56:31.720
She smiled at him.

56:31.720 --> 56:39.720
It was a nice smile, but Nick knew all about nice smiles.

56:39.720 --> 56:49.720
I'm not hungry, he said, and he walked quickly out of the restaurant.

